This is the orginal ammunition that was briefly available to the public in 2004, before F/N voluntarily stopped selling it to civilians. This is ammo that caused a lot of negative publicity for F/N when it first came out. Anti-gun groups claimed it was type IIIA kevlar defeating. I have for Sale / Maybe trade; an all original Springfield M-1 Garand Rifle 30.06, The serial number shows a production date of May 1944, I have had a gunsmith take this rifle totally apart and ensure me that it’s an all original  5/1944 parts.
